Description:
Website: http://sjchistoricalsociety.com/contact/

Type of Organization: Musuem

Address: 31831 Los Rios Street San Juan Capistrano, CA 92675

Phone: (949) 493-8444

Contact Email: museum@capistranohistory.org

Contact Person: Jan Siegel

Latino Materials: Newspapers, Photographs, Artifacts, Books, Pamphlets, Newsletters, Audio Visual, Manuscripts, structures

Details: Mission town founded by St. Junipero Serra, 7th in California Mission chain. They have thousands of photographs and hundreds of artifacts, books, pamphlets, etc. Their location is on the oldest residential street in California. On the street is the oldest house in California with the same family living in it. The current owner's children are 10th generation living in that house. They are Hispanic. They are currently preserving an adobe house from 1840 on our property, built by an Hispanic and they will use it to highlight our artifacts of that period which was the Mexican period in California. Hispanic culture is the core of the community. Spanish, Mexican, Basque have all played an integral part of their history.
